<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-332] nightly build/javadocs for sandbox</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-332</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;This isn&apos;t something i think is crucial, but since i&apos;ve been on the lucene-users&lt;br/&gt;
mailing list (less then 2 months) I&apos;ve seen several people post questions asking&lt;br/&gt;
where they can find documentation on some module available in the sandbox.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the answer of course is usually that they should download the source and build&lt;br/&gt;
the javadocs themselves, but since it keeps coming up, I figured i&apos;d suggest&lt;br/&gt;
setting up a nightly &quot;build&quot; of the whole sandbox, including the javadocs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if nothing else, it will cut down on the number of questions &amp;#8211; but i think it&lt;br/&gt;
may also have an added benefit to the size of the user base.  In my experience,&lt;br/&gt;
people tend to be more willing to download/install something and try it out&lt;br/&gt;
after they&apos;ve read the docs online.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Windows XP&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
